description:
&lt;p&gt;OPMH Staff Nurse Vacancies!!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a passionate, motivated and innovative OPMH nurse? Larch Ward are looking for people like you to join us on the journey to providing outstanding care and support to service users, carers and their families in West Sussex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We here at Meadowfield are excited at the prospect of developing our service further and building upon the recent ‘Good’ CQC rating across Acute services, with recognition of ‘Outstanding’ in the caring domain&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Larch Ward is a mixed gender OPMH ward, made up of 18 beds. All 3 wards at Meadowfield operate with open doors. This is something we are incredibly proud of, and often contributes to positive comments about the atmosphere here on any of the wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sussex is characterised by one of the highest proportion of older adults in the UK with over 21% of the population over 65 years of age, more than half of whom are over 75. As a result it is of particular importance that the Trust ensures its services work well for this expanding patient group and we would love for you to be part of this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced and newly qualified mental health nurses who are motivated, dynamic and forward thinking. You will have a commitment to maintaining and improving service user centered care to the highest standards. Working as part of the multi-disciplinary team you will be able to demonstrate sound communication and clinical skills and be willing to develop these. In return you will benefit from working in a therapeutic environment conducive to the treatment and recovery of older people with acute functional mental health problems as well as experience physical health nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All your skills and training will be fully utilised and developed through clinical supervision and training opportunities including a preceptorship academy for newly qualified nurses and modules offered by the University of Surrey and University of Brighton as well as Trust essential training and an Emerging Leadership Course. There are plenty of opportunities for career development in one of the largest Mental Health Trusts in the South of England.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers the Trust&#39;s £2000 Golden Hello for band 5 or 6 Nurses, or a relocation package up to a maximum of £2000 (subject to terms and conditions).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
